{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:40:49.668Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-wc1r"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-599: git merge driver + documented workflow for append-only history/*.jsonl (concurrent appends fork the hash chain)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":""},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["history","merge","multi-agent"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:40:49.668Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:40:49.668Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"Union-style git merge driver (or documented gitattributes strategy) ships for history/*.jsonl preserving hash-chain repairability; concurrent same-item appends on two branches merge without manual conflict resolution; post-merge chain state is either valid or flagged by validate/health with a history-repair hint; workflow documented"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-g5sx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-3z0k","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-19T03:40:49.668Z"},{"id":"pm-klo8","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-19T03:40:49.668Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"85f87ef282d3a817baf684bb773381978807c96b3c2af8c89e72ae36406bfb1e","message":""}
{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:42:49.748Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GH-599. history/<id>.jsonl is append-only + hash-chained — ideal for conflict-free merging — but no merge driver/gitattributes ships, so concurrent same-item appends on two branches produce a content conflict; naive union leaves a forked hash chain needing manual history-repair. Fix direction: ship a union merge driver that re-anchors the chain deterministically (or documents gitattributes union + mandatory post-merge history-repair), plus post-merge detection wiring per pm-g5sx AC. Coordinate with pm-gpo7 (repair must not silently discard) and pm-ol3p (verify gate)."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:42:49.748Z"}],"before_hash":"85f87ef282d3a817baf684bb773381978807c96b3c2af8c89e72ae36406bfb1e","after_hash":"a525cfd77183db714551c5d4a2f8a794ba994b9376f870c7e0edcf79ae8ab99a"}
